properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover for Pan American Airways, first South Pacific route survey flight, Auckland - San Francisco, accompanied by information sheet (b).a. envelope: Cadbury Fry Hudson Ltd stationery; postmarked March 30, 1937 in Auckland with cancellation mark over red 1-cent stamp at upper right, purple 3-cent stamp at left; hand addressed to Mr. C.V. Smith, Mess Cadbury Fry Hudson Ltd Auckland New Zealand; “By Air Mail / Par Avion” label at upper left; writing in same hand at top edge "per American Clipper - First Flight New Zealand to U.S.A; signed by Captain Edwin Musick.b. information sheet: 8 1/2 x 11 with black text; additional information prepared by donor, including outbound and inbound stops; flight cover was received mounted to sheet with photo corners.Identified by donor with additional information: "Departed March 17, 1937 (the same time Amelia Earhart on her first around the world trip) Only five pieces of mail exist on the southbound flight and fewer than 10 pieces of mail on the return flight from New Zealand. Signed by Capt. Musick but taken away from Musick in San Francisco by Charles Young and allegedly destroyed so they would not violate the rules not to carry mail."
